cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.IT, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the security and privacy of encrypted data formats, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of minimizing information leakage, and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of designing encrypted data formats. Additionally, it touches on the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it discusses the risks of metadata leakage. Finally, the paper proposes a novel padding scheme, which could potentially fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
